To begin a proceeding to recover from the Guaranty Fund, a claimant shall submit to the Division's mediation unit a written complaint that states:
the amount claimed based on the actual loss;
the facts giving rise to the claim;
whether there is other evidence that supports the claim, including expert reports, photographs, or videotapes and that the evidence is included with the complaint;
what documents are related to the claim and that copies of the documents are attached, including the contract of sale; and
any other information that the Division requires.
